Risk-patients for diabetes or patients that are diagnosed with this condition but who are not treated with insulin are randomized two times, according to diet and according to the type of support: Randomization with regard to carbohydrate restriction (25-30 E% or < 10E%).

 Randomization with regard to type of psychological support.

 Either according to Acceptance and Commitment Therapy or to traditional cognitive behavioral therapy.

 Both kinds of psychological support is given as group therapy.

 Two-hundred patients are recruited and each patient is followed for two years.

